# Database Rules

## Role
PostgreSQL is the single source of truth for all persistent data.

## Core principles
- All domain data must be stored in backend-controlled models
- No direct DB access outside backend services

## Data ownership
Backend owns:
- users
- dreams
- sessions
- analyses
- subscriptions

## Session lifecycle contract
- Backend API layer owns DreamSession lifecycle
- Bot and Mini App must never compute session lifecycle logic
- Only backend services decide when to create or reuse a DreamSession
- Every Dream must belong to a DreamSession

## Schema rules
- Use UUID primary keys
- Always include created_at
- Prefer immutable records for analysis history

## Access rules
- Only services/ layer can access DB
- routers must NOT contain DB logic

## Migrations
- All schema changes must go through Alembic
- No manual DB edits

## Anti-patterns
- ❌ bot writing to DB
- ❌ AI writing to DB directly
- ❌ frontend mutation of state

## Design philosophy
Database stores events and states, not UI logic.